# Quick Capture Command

When the user's message starts with "qqq", "quick", or "quick:" followed by text, **only capture — do not organize**.

1. Create a note at `Quick Capture/YYYY-MM-DD — <short descriptive title>.md` using today's date
2. Use this format:

```markdown
---
created: "YYYY-MM-DD"
tags: []
---

# <Short descriptive title>

<user's captured text>
```

3. Confirm what was captured. That's it — don't move it, don't process it, don't touch daily notes.

The note stays in `Quick Capture/` until the user runs **organize**.
